☠ MORTAL KEYS — The Keyboard Slayer
Retro arcade-style piano keyboard trainer inspired by Mortal Kombat. 8 game modes across Identification and Construction. Global leaderboard powered by Firebase. Sister game to Mortal Frets.
🎮 Play Now

Game Modes
All modes: 10 questions per round · Score = errors (fewer = better) · Tiebreaker: time
Identification — see the question on the keyboard, press the correct button
ModeWhat you seeWhat you doNote IDOne key highlighted (2 octaves: Do3–Si4)Press the correct note nameInterval IDR (root, green) + interval key (orange)Press the correct interval (m2–P8)Chord IDClose voicing shown on keyboard (all inversions)Press the correct chord typeScale IDScale notes highlighted in an octave box, R = Root (red)Press the correct scale name
Construction — target illuminated, click keys to build it, press SUBMIT
ModeWhat you seeWhat you doNote ConstructionTarget note illuminatedPlace both occurrences (one per octave)Interval ConstructionR pre-placed (green), interval illuminatedClick the nearest note above R — auto-checks immediatelyChord ConstructionOne chord tone pre-placed (amber, with role label)Click remaining tones in any order, no duplicatesScale ConstructionR pre-placed (red) in octave boxFill all scale notes within the box

Rules

Variety: same type appears at most twice per round; exact same question never repeats
Wrong answer (ID): retry same question, timer keeps running
Wrong SUBMIT (Construction): wrong keys highlighted; fix and re-SUBMIT
Mercy ☠: activates after 2 wrong answers — hold to reveal solution, release to retry
Octave box: Chord and Scale modes — fixed octave range (Do–Do, Re–Re…) or 💀 KHAOS (random each question)
Notation: toggle A-B-C / Do-Re-Mi at any time (default: Do-Re-Mi)


Active Chords & Scales
Before starting, deselect chord or scale types to skip. Deselected types show ✕ in the lobby and in-game. The leaderboard supports two views: ALL (everyone) or SAME CONFIG (only entries with your same selection).

Scoring
ErrorsResult0⚡ FLAWLESS VICTORY1–2EXCELLENT3–5SKILLED6–10FIGHT HARDER11–19FINISH HIM20+FATALITY

Music Theory Coverage
Notes: all 12 chromatic, 2 octaves (Do3–Si4)
Intervals: m2 · M2 · m3 · M3 · P4 · TT · P5 · m6 · M6 · m7 · M7 · P8
Chords: Maj · min · Aug · Dim · Maj7 · Dom7 · min7 · ø7 · °7
Scales: Major · Natural Minor · Harmonic Minor · Melodic Minor · Whole-Half Dim · Half-Whole Dim
Voicings: close voicing, all inversions. Bass note placed in selected octave box; upper notes ascend from bass within keyboard range.

Deploy

Upload mortal_keys.html renamed as index.html
GitHub Settings → Pages → branch main → / (root)


Firebase Setup
Uses same Firebase project as Mortal Frets, separate path mortalkeys/.

Add to Firebase Realtime Database Rules:

json{
  "rules": {
    "leaderboards": {
      "$mode": { ".read": true, ".write": true }
    },
    "mortalkeys": {
      "leaderboards": {
        "$mode": { ".read": true, ".write": true }
      }
    }
  }
}

Replace FB_CONFIG in the <script> tag with your project values (same as Mortal Frets).


Tech
Pure HTML/CSS/JS · Web Audio API · SVG keyboard (2 octaves) · Firebase REST API · Press Start 2P + Rajdhani · CRT scanlines · iOS silent switch bypass via MediaStream API
